==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nasalize
<hw>Na"sal*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Nasalized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Nasalizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To
render nasal, as sound; to insert a nasal or sound in.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nasalize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nasalize
<hw>Na"sal*ize</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To utter words or letters
with a nasal sound; to speak through the nose; to pronounce with a
lowered velum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nasally</ent>⟦br⟧
